locality: Río Zongo Valley, 21 km below dam at Lago Zongo. Low cloud forest with trees 4-6 m tall. Abundant epiphytes, especially mosses and liverworts.
Dept. Cochabamba, Prov. Chapare. Cochabamba-Aguirre-Todos Santos road, between Comercocha and Palmar, about 70 km SW of Todos Santos (air dist.) at km 97, 101, 102, and 104.
22 km NE (below) Unduavi on road to Yolosa Junction (Coroico). Moist forest below cloud forest.
1,5 Km E of Unduavi; on old road which climbs to the new highway.
19.8 km E of pass between Mururata and Illimani. Grassland with clumps of shrubs. Land heavily used for fields and grazing.
Dpto. Cochabamba: Prov. Carrasco. 63.5 km al este del puente sobre el Río Pucara (Punata) por el camino entre Cochabamba y Santa Cruz (9.2 km al oeste del camino a Pocona).
Parque Nacional Carrasco. Entrada de la localidad de Monte Punku-Sehuencas 2 km aproximadamente.

Río Mina Jahuira - - River which runs from Mina Vieja with its mouth 0.5 km N of Choquetanga. Mostly mattoral with trees in the ravine. Barnadesia, Brachyotus, Miconia and Alnus common on the slopes; Hesperomeles found along the river.
